# Css Styling Rule

When creating stylings for a html file, you should:

- stay minimal, organized, consistent, cool, rational and serious
- use elegant and mathematical consistent alignents, fontsizes and spacing
- keep font size small and use compact width instead of medium

For font-family, you should:

- for headings and titles, use "Cormorant Garamond, serif" 
- for code, use "Fira Code"
- for body, use "iosevka"
- for other elements, use different fonts that are in consistent with these fonts

Here is the palette you should use:

```css
:root {
    --bg-color: #ffffff;
    --text-color: #2c3e50;
    --accent-color: #3498db;
    --accent-color-dark: #2980b9;
    --link-color: #2980b9;
    --border-color: #ecf0f1;
    --code-bg: #f8f9fa;
    --callout-bg: #f8f9fa;
    --callout-border: #e9ecef;
    --heading-color: #34495e;
    --list-marker: #3498db;
}

[data-theme="dark"] {
    --bg-color: #1a1a1a;
    --text-color: #ecf0f1;
    --accent-color: #3498db;
    --accent-color-dark: #2980b9;
    --link-color: #3498db;
    --border-color: #2c3e50;
    --code-bg: #2c3e50;
    --callout-bg: #2c3e50;
    --callout-border: #34495e;
    --heading-color: #bdc3c7;
    --list-marker: #3498db;
}
```



